  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dda \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 63477\u0d9a \u0dad\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dca\u0db6\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "63,477 crores in cash crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Knowing that there is a foreign currency crisis in the country, in the year 2020, only 63,477 crores of Sri Lankan money was spent to import various non-essential goods (thorambal goods) in a study conducted by the Department of Economics and Statistics of the University of Peradeniya, according to Professor Wasantha Athukorala. He told Lankadeepa on Sunday.",
        "The professor said that most of these goods are non-essential and can be produced in this country. He also stated that with the money spent on importing these unnecessary goods, it was possible to import nearly 100 oil tankers.",
        "According to the information revealed in this study, 215 crore rupees for pencils, pens, erasers and ink ribbons, 984 crore rupees for toys including kites, 31 crores for hair combs, 35 crores for coir straws, 55 crores for water bottles and weapons. 95 crores, 655 crores for shoes, umbrellas, hats, 956 crores for cleaning products including soaps, 1775 crores for perfume creams, 74 crores for fruit juices, 336 crores for cheese and butter, 18,382 crores for vegetables and fruits (nine hundred and twenty four million dollars) Miscellaneous Information has been revealed in the survey that 1869 crores were spent on furniture, 19,000 crores on auto parts, 493 crores on animal skins and 18522 crores on plastic and rubber.",
        "Prof. Wasantha Athukorala further said that 19 oil tankers were able to be purchased with the amount of 18,382 crore rupees spent on vegetables, two oil tankers with the amount of 1869 crore rupees spent on importing furniture and 19 oil tankers with the amount of 18522 crore rupees spent on importing plastic and rubber."
      ],
